&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Awesome is a free window manager that runs on top of the X Window system on UNIX-type machines. Its goal is to remain very lightweight and offer several window layouts: maximized, floating, but also automatically placed in the form of tiles (a mode called tiling), similar to Ion.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Enabling and Disabling Screen Savers from Command Line</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Activer_Desactiver_ecran_veille_ligne_commande/</link><pubDate>Thu, 31 Jul 2008 10:21:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Activer_Desactiver_ecran_veille_ligne_commande/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>For my job, we got nice 42-inch LCD screens for monitoring. However, these are Toshiba models that don&amp;rsquo;t even include a timer for turning the displays on and off. Instead of manually turning them on and off every morning, I preferred to use screen saver activation and deactivation features to manage them automatically.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="usage">Usage &lt;a href="#usage" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Here&amp;rsquo;s a test that should turn off your screen, wait, and then turn it back on:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Fluxbox: Rounded Corners for All Windows</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Fluxbox_:_Arrondir_les_bords_de_toutes_les_fen%C3%AAtres/</link><pubDate>Thu, 22 Nov 2007 07:20:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Fluxbox_:_Arrondir_les_bords_de_toutes_les_fen%C3%AAtres/</guid><description>&lt;p>Edit &lt;code>/usr/share/fluxbox/styles/&lt;/code>&lt;strong>current_theme_name&lt;/strong>, and insert these lines:&lt;/p>



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="88c7ac0" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>menu.roundCorners: topleft topright bottomleft bottomright
window.roundCorners: topleft topright bottomleft bottomrondie
toolbar.roundCorners: topleft topright bottomleft bottomrondie&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
